<p>President Trump has confirmed that the entirety of the White House East Wing is being torn down and modernized to make room for a new ballroom after demolition work began earlier this week, a White House official said [theglobeandmail.com#1][pbs.org#1][scmp.com#1]. The project has drawn attention because Mr Trump had previously said the ballroom would not &quot;interfere with the current building,&quot; while reporting on costs has varied, with figures cited around $250 million and higher in other reports [bbc.com#1][firstpost.com#1][reddit.com#1]. The White House described the work as a modernization and renovation to support the ballroom project; officials said demolition crews began removing parts of the East Wing this week [theglobeandmail.com#1][pbs.org#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/CPIHuun6MK2ljk45SH7xkhrBXMdjMZN1xctgX_lkGX0iSzqUXcndBK3ptg-UtpTRqhd1jixBYvkH3jJO7wp47MC1aVlP4C_xy1CQ9MzE67IJAi_8VqPBISv6N3Eg2uAdeikpzn3uOKe4mPJfkkwSmByytqNmj5h8pIVIIZ8HNWPxq9F2D0_MG5aQZz42gLnQYEUQJ-CBWcNWTz9938y7kENELqhHVh3lbyS0DXdbGio8G2pLN-7gFxCGv96H9UWqHl3BgftoWE_f1gP9UQ' alt='Heavy machinery tears down a section of the East Wing of the White House to make way for construction on President Donald Trump&#x27;s planned ballroom in Washington on Oct. 22, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Office disruption: The East Wing contains offices used by the first lady and support staff, so the demolition affects their workspace and operations during the renovation [theglobeandmail.com#1].</li><li>Rising cost reports: Different outlets reported varying price tags for the ballroom, with commonly cited figures around $250 million but some reports and social posts suggesting costs have grown to $260–$300 million [firstpost.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][reddit.com#1].</li><li>Administration rationale: President Trump told reporters he had done extensive study with architects and concluded that a full teardown and modernization of the East Wing was needed to support the ballroom addition [scmp.com#1].</li><li>Public reaction: Some commentators and media coverage described sadness and criticism about the scale of changes to a historic presidential building after earlier promises the work would not alter the White House structure [straitstimes.com#2][bbc.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Really a tremendous amount of study with some of the best architects in the world - President Donald Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>White House official: We can confirm that the entire East Wing is going to be modernized and renovated to, I guess, support the... ballroom project. (<a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/us-politics/article-trumps-white-house-ballroom-will-result-in-demolition-of-east-wing/'>The Globe and Mail</a>)</li><li>President Trump: He told reporters he had undertaken &#x27;really a tremendous amount of study with some of the best architects in the world&#x27; to justify the plan. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3330010/trump-confirms-full-demolition-white-house-east-wing-huge-ballroom'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Critics and commentators: Some critics expressed sadness and disappointment that the East Wing would be torn down after earlier assurances the ballroom would not interfere with the building. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/united-states/white-houses-east-wing-will-be-torn-down-fully-to-make-way-for-trump-ballroom'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>Investigative reporters: Journalists and commentators have questioned who will pay for the project and tracked varying cost estimates around the ballroom addition. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/who-is-paying-for-trumps-big-beautiful-ballroom-at-the-white-house-13944415.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/czxn7lwzx5po'>Trump says &#x27;existing structure&#x27; of White House East Wing to be torn down</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='